v:4 c:$ m:T07-shareable-room-link role:dev x:vue3/url
gate: LOCKED

task: Make the room shareable via URL so a second player joins the same jam from a link

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
out:
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/composables/useJamSession.ts
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/components/JamControls.vue

context: |
  room is a plain ref in useJamSession (default 'jam-001') with no URL coupling.
  To test multiplayer capture (the whole point of the DAWW3 story) you need a
  frictionless "send a link, friend lands in the same room" path. No router is
  installed — use URL query/hash directly (e.g. ?room=abc), no new dependency.

steps:
  1. On composable init: read room from location (e.g. URLSearchParams ?room=);
     if present, seed room.value with it. Else keep default.
  2. When the user edits room (pre-join), reflect it into the URL via
     history.replaceState so the address bar always shows a shareable link.
  3. JamControls Session section: add a "Copy invite link" button that copies
     the full URL (origin + ?room=<room>) to clipboard via navigator.clipboard,
     with a tiny "Copied" confirmation. Existing styles.
  4. Optional (only if trivial): if no ?room= present, generate a friendly random
     room id instead of the static 'jam-001' so fresh links don't collide.

done:
  - Opening ?room=foo seeds the room field with "foo"
  - Editing the room (before join) updates the URL without reload
  - "Copy invite link" copies a working URL that lands another tab in the same room
  - Verified: two tabs via the same link join the same jam
  - tsc --noEmit passes
